abstract: >
Multi-Wing GPT Autonomy Architecture is a conceptual and architectural
specification for governed structural autonomy in role-based GPT systems.
It defines a staged autonomy model, multi-wing role distribution, safety
layers, governance boundaries, and an action permission model for GPT-based
systems that require role consistency, reviewability, accountability, and
human authority preservation.

